  m_Name: Shirley Wright
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  characterSystem:
    characterName: Shirley Wright
    hejFras: Up for an interview?
    hejFrasEvent:
      Guid:
        Data1: -1969025583
        Data2: 1189526410
        Data3: -259140981
        Data4: -697027641
      Path: event:/Shirley/Shirley Hej
    firstQuestion:
      question: 'What is a reporter doing here? '
      answer: "There\u2019s rumors going around! I thought everyone knew. Have you
        been living under a rock? I\u2019ve been up since early morning preparing,
        now I'm here to snoop and find out what's really going on around here! "
    q1FollowUpQuestion1:
      question: "So tell me, what\u2019s the latest scoop? "
      answer: "I tried to talk to Mr Allford, but all he gave me was gobbledygook!
        More so, I\u2019ve also seen some strange fellows out and about. The police
        constable is here somewhere, also snooping around; some goon from the mob
        is here and is looking real angry; all while that maid over there has had
        her peepers on the exit the whole time!  "
    q1FollowUpQuestion2:
      question: 'How does it all fit together? '
      answer: "My theory was that Mr Allford and the police were in cahoots, but
        why is the constable looking so angry? There\u2019s some real first page
        material here, I know it! "
    secondQuestion:
      question: "Too many geezers here don\u2019t you think? "
      answer: 'Yes, and everyone thinks I am a rookie, even though I just unveiled
        the biggest story this year AND the biggest last year. My pockets are still
        full of sand from my last story. '
    q2FollowUpQuestion1:
      question: "I didn\u2019t see a story about the beach in the paper? "
      answer: "Not a beach! I did a reportage on the annual sand castle competition!
        They move tons of sand from the beach, right to central park so the waves
        don\u2019t destroy the castles! "
    q2FollowUpQuestion2:
      question: 'Sand castle competitions? That sounds like rookie business. '
      answer: "Don\u2019t say that to the sand castle professionals! I would know\u2026
        I still find sand behind the closet\u2026 "
    thirdQuestion:
      question: 'Doing many interviews? '
      answer: 'I was, but unfortunately I made a goof and spilled champagne on my
        notepad. Not many had any gossip about Allford anyways, mostly yucks yapping,
        I feel like a schnook. '
    q3FollowUpQuestion1:
      question: 'Maybe you could investigate my dance moves? '
      answer: "Are you inviting me to a dance? That\u2019s pretty forward of you!
        I\u2019m not someone to shy away from some light hearted flirting. Though
        sadly duty comes first. I have two girls at home to feed. "
    q3FollowUpQuestion2:
      question: "Oh, I didn\u2019t know you had kids? "
      answer: "Kids? Ew\u2026 No, cats! I would do anything for my little babies! "
    "hejD\xE5Fras": 'See you in the papers! '
